dismissalText.commentary: Sulieman Benn c Clarke b Bracken 7 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 116.66

commentTextItems.html: and that's it! It's all over, Clarke runs round from long on to take the catch as the batsman attempted to drive right over for the six

commentPostTextItems.html: So, Australia complete a convincing victory, by 84 runs. Their total always looked daunting in the conditions and indeed West Indies fell away, although they gave their best in patches.

Chris Gayle's being interviewed now and he swears to "bounce back". Here's Ricky Ponting. "Shaun Marsh on his debut game played a beautiful innings. I thought we were a bit sloppy in the field. We expect the younger guys to come in and have some success straight away. It was great to see Shaun out there and looked in good control and he's earned the Man of the Match award today."

Marsh accepts his award. "I probably should have [got the hundred]. It's fantastic to be here. To go well was really good, to get the win was even better. I'm just enjoying every minute of it. To be part of this team is amazing, I'm loving every minute."
Thanks for joining us today and do tune in tomorrow for England's latest ODI with New Zealand and come back later in the week for the next game in this series. Until then, it's goodbye.

commentPreTextItems.html: Oh no, there's some rain in the air. This will never do - it's helpful to nobody. The crowd are annoyed with the whole situation and are throwing cans around and on to the pitch. The third umpire comes round to have a word with the groundstaff. It's not clear what they're protesting at - although it's likely to be the fact that Sammy was waiting on the boundary edge, unhappy with being given out.

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson lbw b Bravo 31 (27b 4x4 0x6 59m) SR: 114.81

dismissalComment.html: a huge shout as Watson walks right across his stumps - something he's been favouring this innings - and the ball comes in , pitching just outside off and rapping him in line with leg, Watson too late on the would-be flick off the legs

dismissalText.commentary: Ricky Ponting b Taylor 5 (20b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: some width right outside off and Ponting looks to slam it to the covers but instead drags a thick inside edge a long way and back onto the sticks

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke c Ramdin b Sammy 9 (23b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 39.13

dismissalComment.html: Clarke's gone! Stepped outside off, tried to run it down to third man and sends a thick outside edge through to Ramdin who takes it two-handed to spark celebrations from Sammy and his team

dismissalText.commentary: Shaun Marsh c Gayle b Sammy 81 (97b 7x4 1x6 129m) SR: 83.5

dismissalComment.html: and there's the breakthrough they wanted! A slightly slower ball in the slot and Marsh drives, can't keep it down and it goes straight to Gayle at cover

dismissalComment.html: comes out and drives straight and hard down the ground and he holes out at long off, Pollard took it well inside the rope - stretching up with two hands to pluck it safe

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Bravo lbw b Clarke 33 (37b 4x4 0x6 51m) SR: 89.18

dismissalComment.html: and he strikes immediately! Bravo takes a long stride forward, misses the ball, and he's caught in front. West Indies are four down now, Bravo could be in some trouble as he stood there for a while shaking his head but there was no problem with the ball itself which would have gone on to hit middle and leg

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard c Haddin b Johnson 11 (20b 0x4 1x6 30m) SR: 55

dismissalComment.html: and he strikes! Johnson pushes it across him, Pollard edges off the back foot fending away from his body and Haddin snaps up the chance

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin b Watson 31 (38b 1x4 0x6 55m) SR: 81.57

dismissalComment.html: cleans him up now, comprehensively. The ball's a peach, nipping right back in from outside off and the batsman drove right at it, going through the gate

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy b Bracken 33 (35b 2x4 0x6 59m) SR: 94.28

dismissalComment.html: bowled him - although he needed confirmation from the umpire as to whether it came off Haddin's pads or the stumps, both as it happened - Sammy swishing at the air

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jerome Taylor c Haddin b Bracken 11 (10b 0x4 1x6 11m) SR: 110

dismissalComment.html: slower ball, and the batsman's all mixed up there, looking to play it out to the leg side but his leading edge pops up towards gully, Haddin calls it and carries on over to collect with two hands

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Bracken player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sulieman Benn c Clarke b Bracken 7 (6b 1x4 0x6 9m) SR: 116.66

dismissalComment.html: and that's it! It's all over, Clarke runs round from long on to take the catch as the batsman attempted to drive right over for the six
